{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#5700: Compiler should warn about duplicate/conditional slots",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:26:28.266284+00:00",
  "text": "Compiler should warn about duplicate/conditional slots\n\n### Version\r\n3.2.31\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[vue-next-template-explorer.netlify.app](https://vue-next-template-explorer.netlify.app/#)\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\nLook at the AST for the SFC. In the dev console, you can see the component has only one child. \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13410410/162804875-076d563b-7fce-49f8-8a2e-afbc9b16bf10.png)\r\n\r\nThe workaround example (from below) has the part that is missing. `branches` is present for conditional rendering\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13410410/162804980-ce96a300-2bb4-46e4-bde7-09b4d525c965.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nBoth named-slots are registered in the AST.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nOnly one of the conditional templates with named slots is registered in the AST. The second is not.\r\n\r\n---\r\nReference: https://github.com/johnsoncodehk/volar/issues/1150\r\n\r\nWorkaround: not put a condition on template of named slot but instead make the content conditional\r\n\r\n#### SFC that generates bad AST\r\n```vue\r\n<script\r\n  setup\r\n  lang=\"ts\"\r\n>\r\n  import { ref } from 'vue';\r\n  import ComponentWithSlots from '@/src/foobar';\r\n\r\n  const aVariableThatExists = ref(true);\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n<template>\r\n  <ComponentWithSlots>\r\n    <template\r\n      #content\r\n      v-if=\"aVariableThatExists\"\r\n    >\r\n      <div>{{ aVariableThatExists }}</div>\r\n    </template>\r\n    <template\r\n      #content\r\n      v-else\r\n    >\r\n      <div>{{ thisVariableDoesNotExist }}</div>\r\n      <div>{{ thisShouldBeUnderlinedInRed }}</div>\r\n    </template>\r\n  </ComponentWithSlots>\r\n</template>\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Workaround SFC\r\nMove the conditional logic into the children of a single slotted template. Define an extra set of template tags that the conditional logic can live on:\r\n```vue\r\n<script\r\n  setup\r\n  lang=\"ts\"\r\n>\r\n  import { ref } from 'vue';\r\n  import ComponentWithSlots from '@/src/foobar';\r\n\r\n  const aVariableThatExists = ref(true);\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n<template>\r\n  <ComponentWithSlots>\r\n    <template\r\n      #content\r\n    >\r\n      <template v-if=\"aVariableThatExists\">\r\n        <div>{{ aVariableThatExists }}</div>\r\n      </template>\r\n      <template v-else>\r\n        <div>{{ thisVariableDoesNotExist }}</div>\r\n      </template>\r\n    </template>\r\n  </ComponentWithSlots>\r\n</template>\r\n```\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request",
    "scope: compiler"
  ],
